data.text: @HerSoulWrites Didn’t her mama live to 100? Spite can keep you alive a long time tho 😂

The Queen has never, ever, eveeeeeerrrrrrrrr seen it for Duchess Camila. She doesn't want her in a particular position of power. 

I'm convinced it's why she (the Queen) refuses to die.

Sidenote: I don't see Prince Charles really accepting the responsibilities of the throne & Crown. At all. 

He's been attached to too many scandalous instances. Too many. 

The biggest one being that he defied his mother by "marrying down" AFTER he was divorced from Princess Di.

And that is the "GOTCHA!"

They wanted to make it so that Princess Diana wouldn't interfere with Royal Dealings BUT ended up with a damn BOGO thanks to her sons (and now both of their wives). 

Princess Diana gets the last laugh after all.
@HerSoulWrites I honestly feel like that’s a big possibility.
@orchidassassin Yup. And as quiet as it's kept? I actually wouldn't be surprised if Prince Charles actually refused his right to the Throne.

And true humanitarians are the people they need to keep away from the Crown because that energy would shake the table. 

Too bad so sad though for the Crown though. Princess Di was ADORED by her sons. All of their actions and the work they did has her imprint on it.

@HerSoulWrites And it’s pretty likely Kate will end up queen, just even on logistics. Charles is about to be 70. Those folks seem to live a long ass time, but still. She’ll be queen in her lifetime I’m sure.

And that's what's crazy to me. I'd bet money the Queen was smitten by Princess Diana because they had a likeness in temperament. 

Basically? The Queen loved that Princess Di was her own person even at 19. The thing she didn't foresee was that Princess Di was a true humanitarian.

The Crown, Parliament, and all other forms of government would have to adjust in a way they wouldn't want to.

Because there is NO WAY Princess Di's impact (on the world) would not influence how they govern.

But the thing that really gets me -

The kind of woman Prince William and Prince Harry decided to marry is very telling. Because let's say the Queen passes away and her son Prince Charles gives up the throne?

Do you know the impact a true public servant will leave on the Crown?

When Princess Di passed away, I think it was her brother who publicly remarked that HER family would continue to raise them the way she wanted them to be raised. 

The video I retweeted detailing how she broke protocol reminded me of that.
